## Attachment A: Standard Terms & Conditions

### 4.1 Fees, Expenses, Payment
Client shall pay Texas Pulmonary & Critical Care Consultants, PA ("TPCCC") the professional fees in accordance with the Statement of Work. The daily rate of one thousand dollars ($1,000) is inclusive of all services and expenses. Payment is expected within forty-five (45) days of submission of invoice, unless otherwise agreed to in writing by both parties.

### 4.2 Confidentiality
TPCCC acknowledges that all materials disclosed to it by Client, and the work it provides to Client, are confidential and proprietary. TPCCC will abide by all reasonable restrictions placed by Client on the dissemination of such materials and work. In the event that TPCCC is served with a subpoena or other legal document requesting the disclosure of such materials or work, TPCCC will promptly advise Client of same and will cooperate with all reasonable and lawful requests by Client to prevent the disclosure of confidential and/or proprietary information pursuant to such subpoena or other request.

- TPCCC is being entrusted with Privileged Health Information (PHI) protected under both Texas and federal HIPAA Privacy Regulations. TPCCC will execute a Business Associate Agreement (BAA) with the Client if that has not already been completed.
- This section shall not apply to information which is (i) publicly known, (ii) already known to the recipient; (iii) disclosed to a third party without restriction; (iv) independently developed; or (v) disclosed pursuant to legal requirement or order. Subject to the foregoing, TPCCC may disclose Client's confidential information to its subcontractors and affiliates.
- Neither party shall use the other party's name or refer to the other party directly or indirectly in any media release, public announcement, or public disclosure relating to this engagement without written consent from the other party for each such use or release. Notwithstanding the foregoing, TPCCC may use Client's name in experience citations and recruiting materials.

### 4.3 Conflicts of Interest
Based on the information provided by Client, TPCCC is not aware of circumstances that constitute a conflict of interest or that would otherwise impair its ability to provide objective assistance. Parties may retain TPCCC with interests that may not be consistent with those of Client, provided the substance of the work does not create an actual conflict.

### 4.4 Limitations on Liability
The total liability of TPCCC, its officers, employees, and agents for all claims of any kind arising out of this engagement, whether in contract, tort or otherwise, shall be limited to the total fees paid to TPCCC on this engagement. Neither party shall in any event be liable to the other for any indirect, consequential, or punitive damages. TPCCC shall not be liable for any loss or destruction of any documents provided to TPCCC, and Client shall be responsible for insuring such documents against loss or destruction.

### 4.5 Use of Deliverables
TPCCC is providing the Services and Deliverables solely for Client's internal use and benefit. Client may disclose Deliverables or discuss information relating to Services with professional advisors and subcontractors with a need to know such information, provided they are subject to obligations of confidentiality. Client may not disclose or make reference to TPCCC, the Deliverables, or Services to other third parties without TPCCC's prior written consent.

### 4.6 Resolution of Disputes
Neither TPCCC nor Client shall institute a proceeding before any court to resolve any controversy or claim ("dispute") arising out of or relating to this engagement until the parties have sought to resolve the dispute through direct, good faith negotiation. If the dispute is not resolved within thirty (30) days, the parties shall attempt to resolve the dispute through non-binding mediation. All mediation proceedings hereunder shall be held in Tarrant County, Texas.

### 4.7 Independent Contractor Status
TPCCC shall provide services as an independent contractor, and none of its employees or independent contractors shall be an employee of Client.

### 4.8 Governing Law
This Agreement shall be construed and interpreted according to, and the rights of the parties shall be governed by, the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to conflicts of law principles.

### 4.9 Entire Agreement
This engagement letter and its attachments represent the entire agreement between the parties regarding the subject matter and supersede any prior understandings or agreements. Any changes must be agreed to in writing.
